---
---

<section id="infrastructure" class="section-surface-strong">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Infrastructure</p>
      <h2>Infrastructure planned for rollout, operations, and growth.</h2>
      <p>
        CloudBridge builds satellite-based infrastructure for African hospitals, institutions,
        businesses, and remote sites that need dependable service.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="infrastructure-visual card" aria-label="CloudBridge build path">
      <div class="infrastructure-visual-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">What we build</p>
        <h3>From satellite backhaul to live site operations.</h3>
        <p>
          Each deployment is designed as one connected delivery path, not separate vendors
          for the link, the local network, and the systems that keep service running.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="infrastructure-track" aria-hidden="true">
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="build-grid">
        <article class="build-step">
          <div class="build-step-top">
            <p class="build-step-index">01</p>
            <p class="build-step-label">Network layer</p>
          </div>
          <h3>Satellite backhaul</h3>
          <p>Primary connectivity for remote and underserved sites.</p>
          <div class="build-step-rows">
            <div>
              <span>Link type</span>
              <strong>Primary satellite route</strong>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span>Best for</span>
              <strong>Weak terrestrial coverage</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="build-step">
          <div class="build-step-top">
            <p class="build-step-index">02</p>
            <p class="build-step-label">Control layer</p>
          </div>
          <h3>Edge and routing</h3>
          <p>On-site equipment configured around traffic, power, and site conditions.</p>
          <div class="build-step-rows">
            <div>
              <span>Handles</span>
              <strong>Traffic and failover</strong>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span>Placed for</span>
              <strong>Site-specific constraints</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="build-step">
          <div class="build-step-top">
            <p class="build-step-index">03</p>
            <p class="build-step-label">Coverage layer</p>
          </div>
          <h3>Site network</h3>
          <p>Coverage across wards, offices, branches, and shared working areas.</p>
          <div class="build-step-rows">
            <div>
              <span>Rollout</span>
              <strong>Indoor and campus coverage</strong>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span>Output</span>
              <strong>Usable service across the site</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="build-step">
          <div class="build-step-top">
            <p class="build-step-index">04</p>
            <p class="build-step-label">Operating layer</p>
          </div>
          <h3>Billing and operations</h3>
          <p>Usage rules, monitoring, and service workflows handled under one system.</p>
          <div class="build-step-rows">
            <div>
              <span>Includes</span>
              <strong>Billing and access control</strong>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span>Keeps</span>
              <strong>Service continuity in view</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <p class="infrastructure-summary">
        CloudBridge stays responsible from first link design to day-to-day service continuity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="capabilities-grid">
      <article class="card capability-card">
        <p class="capability-index">01</p>
        <h3>Satellite backhaul</h3>
        <p>Primary connectivity for facilities where terrestrial options are weak, unstable, or unavailable.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card capability-card">
        <p class="capability-index">02</p>
        <h3>On-site network design</h3>
        <p>Coverage planning for facilities, campuses, branch locations, and high-use operational areas.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card capability-card">
        <p class="capability-index">03</p>
        <h3>Billing and access control</h3>
        <p>Where the project needs it, we handle billing, user access flows, and platform-side operations.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card capability-card">
        <p class="capability-index">04</p>
        <h3>Remote deployment</h3>
        <p>Installations in areas where access, maintenance windows, and logistics need to be thought through carefully.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card capability-card">
        <p class="capability-index">05</p>
        <h3>Monitoring and support</h3>
        <p>Post-deployment follow-up so a live site stays usable after handover.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card capability-card">
        <p class="capability-index">06</p>
        <h3>Ongoing operations</h3>
        <p>Monitoring, issue follow-up, and practical support once the network is in service.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .infrastructure-visual {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-32);
    padding: var(--space-24);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-24);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .infrastructure-visual-header {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .infrastructure-visual-header h3 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.75rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
  }

  .infrastructure-track {
    display: none;
    position: relative;
    height: 20px;
  }

  .infrastructure-track::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 9px;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .infrastructure-track span {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    transform: translateX(-50%);
  }

  .infrastructure-track span:nth-child(1) {
    left: 12.5%;
  }

  .infrastructure-track span:nth-child(2) {
    left: 37.5%;
  }

  .infrastructure-track span:nth-child(3) {
    left: 62.5%;
  }

  .infrastructure-track span:nth-child(4) {
    left: 87.5%;
  }

  .build-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-16);
  }

  .build-step {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-16);
    min-height: 236px;
    padding: var(--space-24);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    background: var(--color-surface-strong);
  }

  .build-step-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .build-step-index,
  .capability-index {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .build-step h3,
  .capability-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .build-step-label {
    color: var(--color-subtle);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .build-step-rows {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  .build-step-rows div {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .build-step-rows span {
    color: var(--color-subtle);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .build-step-rows strong {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .infrastructure-summary {
    padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-24);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    background: var(--color-text);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .capabilities-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-16);
  }

  .capability-card {
    padding: var(--space-24);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .capability-index {
    color: var(--color-subtle);
  }

  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .build-grid,
    .capabilities-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .build-step-rows div {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }

    .build-step-rows strong {
      max-width: 13rem;
      text-align: right;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1080px) {
    .capabilities-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1180px) {
    .infrastructure-track {
      display: block;
    }

    .build-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }
</style>
